<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Phil Barnes Leads PBA Seniors  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SINKING SPRING, Pa. (AP) -- Phil Barnes averaged 247 for eight
games Sunday night, including a 300 game, and held a 79-pin lead
over Joe Hutchinson after the opening round of the PBA Senior
Tour's Central Pennsylvania Senior Open.
</P>
<P>
   Barnes, who has one victory in his six years on the senior tour,
bowled the perfect game in his second of the night. He finished
with a pinfall of 1,979.
</P>
<P>
   Hutchinson, a rookie on the senior tour, was 27 pins in front of
Mike Kilgannon, while Dick Mustain, 1,870, and Ron Winger, 1,859,
rounded out the top five.
</P>
<P>
   The three-squad field of 144 bowlers was to return Monday and
Tuesday for two additional eight-game rounds of qualifying. The top
24 qualifiers will advance to three rounds of match play Wednesday
and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The stepladder finals will be Thursday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
