<DOCNO> APW20000515.0024 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-15 03:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Saints Making Screen Debut  </HEADLINE>
By CLAR NI CHONGHAILE
<TEXT>
<P>
   CANNES, France (AP) -- It's not a big step from music to movies,
but artists have been known to stumble while making it. Not so for
All Saints, making their screen debut in Cannes this week in Dave
Stewart's ''Honest.''
</P>
<P>
   Stewart, best known as Annie Lennox's sidekick in '80s hit band
Eurythmics, turns in a slick, feel-good film for his directorial
debut.
</P>
<P>
   Band members Nicole and Natalie Appleton and Melanie Blatt play
gun-toting, tough-talking sisters, determined to rob their way out
of London's depressed East End during the swinging sixties.
</P>
<P>
   Nicole is Gerry, the responsible ringleader, while Natalie plays
her angry, out-to-shock sister. Melanie makes up the trio as the
younger, wiser sibling.
</P>
<P>
   ''Honest,'' which is competing for the Golden Camera award, will
be officially screened today in Cannes.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   Haley Joel Osment may only be 12 years old, but the actor, who
won an Oscar nomination for his role in ''Sixth Sense'' with Bruce
Willis, is already cruising the Croisette.
</P>
<P>
   Osment jetted into Cannes over the weekend to promote his latest
film, ''Edges of the Lord,'' also starring Willem Dafoe.
</P>
<P>
   The young actor plays a Jewish boy who takes refuge with a
family of Catholic peasant farmers during the Nazi occupation of
Poland. The film is shooting in Poland now.
</P>
<P>
   Osment, whose wide-eyed, mature performance in ''Sixth Sense''
set the industry's talent radars glowing, has also just completed
''Pay It Forward,'' starring Kevin Spacey and Helen Hunt.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   Venezuelan director Fina Torres describes Penelope Cruz, her
leading lady in ''Woman on Top,'' as a ''Latin Audrey Hepburn.''
</P>
<P>
   For the Spanish actress, that's quite a compliment. She adores
Hepburn.
</P>
<P>
   Torres, who is showing ''Woman on Top'' in Cannes, says Cruz was
her first choice for the main character, Isabella.
</P>
<P>
   ''She has all the elements -- she is beautiful, good, fragile,
sensual, innocent and sexy ... When she puts her hair up, she is
like a Latin Audrey Hepburn,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Looking slightly startled by the compliment, Cruz said Hepburn
was one of her idols.
</P>
<P>
   ''I would have loved to have met her. If she was alive now, I'd
go to her hotel and beg, 'Please, please see me.' But she wasn't
perfect, she had a big nose,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Described by Torres as a fable, ''Woman on Top'' is tale of
cooking, music and most of all Brazil. ''I love the force, the
vitality of the people. It's like a love letter to Brazil,'' Torres
said.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   Chinese director Jiang Wen has a couple of tips for dealing with
overzealous censors.
</P>
<P>
   He should know. Chinese censors tried to block his Cannes entry
''Devils on the Doorstep'' from competing. The film is a
tragicomedy set in a tiny Chinese village during the Japanese
occupation.
</P>
<P>
   ''One of the tricks is to invite the censors to dinner or get
them drunk,'' he said, speaking through an interpreter.
</P>
<P>
   Jiang said censors had monitored his film from the outset,
forcing him to change the script five times. Finally, they sent
four or five pages of extra changes to the festival, including a
request for a new title, which Jiang ignored.
</P>
<P>
   ''They didn't want the title to hurt the feelings of ethnic
minorities. But what feelings, whose?'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Devils on the Doorstep'' also stars Jiang as a Chinese
villager who faces disaster when an anti-Japanese faction leaves
two sacks in his home. Inside the sacks are a Japanese
prisoner-of-war and his interpreter.
</P>
<P>
   When food starts running out, the villagers decide to kill the
prisoners but nobody wants to do the deed and the hesitation ends
in tragedy.
</P>
</TEXT>
