<HEADLINE> Limited's 1Q Earnings Rise 41 Pct.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- The Limited Inc.'s first-quarter earnings
rose 41 percent from a year ago, fueled by strength at its women's
clothing stores Express and Limited as well as a surge in profits
at its Intimate Brands division.
</P>
<P>
   The Columbus, Ohio-based retailer reported Monday that it earned
$62.9 million, or 28 cents a share, for the quarter ended April 29,
compared with $44.6 million, or 19 cents a share, a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Sales increased 5 percent to $2.1 billion from $2 billion in the
first quarter of 1999. Sales from stores opened at least a year,
often a key indicator of a retailer's strength, were up 8 percent
for the quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The results topped Wall Street analysts' expectations of 25
cents a share. Its stock, however, was down $1.68} at $47.93} in
early trading on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Limited benefited from an 29 percent increase in profits at
Intimate Brands, which stores include Victoria's Secret and Bath &AMP;
Body Works.
</P>
<P>
   Also boosting profits was improved sales at its Express and
Limited women's clothing stores. The merchandise in both stores
have been overhauled in recent years to better keep pace with
current fashion trends.
</P>
<P>
   This year's results reflect the Limited Too spinoff, a
children's apparel brand, as if it had occurred at the beginning of
1999. The spinoff occurred in August.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this month, the Limited announced a 2-for-1 stock split.
</P>
<P>
   The Limited operates 2,849 stores under the names Express,
Lerner New York, Lane Bryant, Limited, Structure and Henri Bendel.
The Limited also owns about 84 percent of Intimate Brands, which
operates 2,144 stores.
</P>
</TEXT>
