<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Falls  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar rose against the Japanese yen but
fell against the euro today in European trading. Gold prices fell.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar rose to 109.43 Japanese yen from 1.0870 yen late
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   But it fell against the euro, which edged up to 91.37 cents from
90.80 cents late Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar also fell to 1.7020 Swiss francs from 1.7082, but
rose to 1.4891 Canadian dollars from 1.4868. The British pound was
quoted at $1.5081, down from $1.5174.
</P>
<P>
   In midday New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 109.51 yen
and 1.7048 Swiss francs. The euro was quoted at 91.28 cents and the
pound was trading at $1.5064.
</P>
<P>
   Based on euro rates in Europe, the dollar is worth 2.1394 German
marks, down from 2.1535; 7.1736 French francs, down from 7.2194;
2.4100 Dutch guilders, down from 2.4254, and 2,11753 Italian lire,
down from 2,131.05.
</P>
<P>
   Gold closed in London at $275.10 per troy ounce, down from
$276.60 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   In Zurich the bid was $274.70, down from $276.00.
</P>
<P>
   Gold fell 40 cents in Hong Kong to close at $276.25.
</P>
<P>
   Silver closed in London at $4.99 per troy ounce, down from
$5.01.
</P>
</TEXT>
