<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US To Re-Inspect North Korea Site  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP)-- A U.S. team will travel to North Korea for a
second inspection of a site once thought by American officials to
be a headquarters for production of nuclear weapons, the State
Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Spokesman Richard Boucher said the inspection will begin on May
23 at the Kumchang-ni site.
</P>
<P>
   There was no evidence a year ago that the site was being used
for weapons production. The purpose of the second visit is to
confirm the work of the first, Boucher said.
</P>
<P>
   In the 1999 inspection of the underground site, the American
team found only a large tunnel and no equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Under a 1994 agreement with the United States, North Korea
promised not to use nuclear technology for military purposes.
</P>
</TEXT>
