<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Clear to partly cloudy skies prevailed over most of
the easterain
third of the nation Monday, and showers and thunderstorms speckled
the Plains and West Coast.
<TEXT>
<P>
   A few very light rain showers developed over upstate New York,
while skies were clear from the Great Lakes, south through the Ohio
and Tennessee Valley's and into the Mid-Atlantic and Southeast
states. Southeast Georgia and Florida, though, got hit with
scattered showers and thunderstorms.
</P>
<P>
   A warm front continued to lift north across parts of the
southerain Plains. Showers and thunderstorms stretched from easterain
Kansas, southward into northeasterain Oklahoma -- but they were only
are light to moderate.
</P>
<P>
   Fair to partly cloudy skies were seen from westerain Nebraska,
south into Texas.
</P>
<P>
   A few widely scattered showers hit the Northerain Plains, mostly
located across the Dakotas.
</P>
<P>
   A trough of low pressure digging into the West Coast brought
unsettled weather to a chunk of the West. Parts of Washington,
Oregon northerain Califorainia got some rain, while cloudy skies
shrouded the Rockies and Southwest.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures ranged in the Lower 48 on Monday from 90 degree in
Brooksville, Fla., to 38 in Stanley, Idaho.
</P>
</TEXT>
