<HEADLINE> Rangers Activate Catalanotto  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Texas Rangers infielder Frank
Catalanotto was activated Monday from the 15-day disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for him, infielder Tom Evans was placed on the
15-day DL, retroactive to May 11, with right shoulder problems. An
MRI on Friday revealed Evans has a partial tear of his rotator cuff
and a torn labrum in his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   It has not been determined whether Evans, who was batting .278
with five RBIs in 23 games, will have surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Catalanotto pulled his left groin on April 21 and was placed on
the disabled list the following day. He was sent on a
rehabilitation assignment to Triple-A Oklahoma City on Friday. He
is hitting .500 with eight RBIs in nine games with the big-league
club.
</P>
<P>
   Outfielder Rusty Greer was sent to Double-A Tulsa on Monday on a
rehab assignment. Greer, batting .240 with one homer and five RBIs
in seven games, was placed on the 15-day DL on April 13 with a left
hamstring injury and underwent arthroscopic surgery April 16.
</P>
</TEXT>
