<HEADLINE> 'Gladiator' Tops Box Office Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Roman epic ''Gladiator'' ruled the
box-office arena for a second straight weekend, taking in $24.6
million and pushing its total gross to $73.6 million in 10 days of
release.
</P>
<P>
   John Travolta's sci-fi adventure ''Battlefield Earth,'' which
received gleefully vicious reviews, debuted at No. 2 with $11.5
million.
</P>
