<HEADLINE> Timeline of Columbine Attack  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Timeline of the attack on Columbine High School the
morning of
April 20, 1999:
<TEXT>
<P>
   11:14: Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold plant bombs in the school
cafeteria. The primary device fails to explode.
</P>
<P>
   11:19: Shouting ''Go! Go!'' the gunmen start shooting from the
top of the stairs leading into the west side of the school. First
shots kill two students outside the school.
</P>
<P>
   11:21: Jefferson County sheriff's dispatcher receive report of
an explosion in a field near the school, a diversionary ploy by the
gunmen.
</P>
<P>
   11:23: The first 911 call is made from the school.
</P>
<P>
   11:24: School resource officer Neal Gardner responds and
exchanges gunfire with Harris.
</P>
<P>
   11:26: First police car arrives. Teacher Dave Sanders is shot
inside the school.
</P>
<P>
   11:27: A pipe bomb goes off in the cafeteria. The gunmen enter
the library and begin killing students there.
</P>
<P>
   11:35: The gunmen fire the last shot that kills a victim.
</P>
<P>
   11:44: Harris and Klebold return to the cafeteria and shoot at
bombs but fail to detonate them. A witness hears one gunman say,
''Today, the world's going to come to an end. Today's the day we
die.''
</P>
<P>
   11:46: A bomb partially explodes in the cafeteria. A second bomb
partially detonates a minute later.
</P>
<P>
   Noon: Gunmen return to the library.
</P>
<P>
   12:06: One of two makeshift SWAT teams enters the school and the
second follows.
</P>
<P>
   12:08: Harris and Klebold kill themselves.
</P>
<P>
   2:30: SWAT teams begin freeing students in hiding.
</P>
<P>
   2:40: SWAT teams reach teacher Dave Sanders but are unable to
remove him.
</P>
<P>
   3:22: First SWAT team reaches the library.
</P>
<P>
   4:30: SWAT teams declare school under control.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-15-00 2012 </TRAILER>
