<HEADLINE> Security Up for Devils-Flyers Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Security for Game 2 of the Eastern
Conference finals between the New Jersey Devils and Philadelphia
Flyers will be increased because of an ugly fight in the stands
late in the opening game of the series.
</P>
<P>
   The Flyers and officials from Comcast-Spectacor, which operates
First Union Center, said in a release Monday that the extra
security will be on hand because of the potential problems with the
''turnpike'' series with the Devils.
</P>
