<HEADLINE> Mariners' Moyer Throws for Practice  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Seattle Mariners left-hander Jamie Moyer,
sidelined with a strained muscle in his left shoulder, threw 60
practice pitches including 40 off the mound at Safeco Field on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time Moyer pitched since being placed on the
15-day disabled list retroactive to April 15.
</P>
<P>
   Mariners officials said it is still uncertain when Moyer will
return.
</P>
<P>
   Right-hander Freddy Garcia, also a starter, was off crutches
Monday, but team officials said they also don't know when he'll
pitch. Garcia went on the 15-day disabled list April 22 with a
hairline fracture of his right tibia.
</P>
</TEXT>
